  "title": "Infinite Loop in routing for react-instantsearch",
  "body": "Hi, \r\n\r\nI am trying to work out my routing and it seems like when I setState my searchState inside onSearchStateChange, my components goes into infinite loop.\r\n\r\nHere is my code. \r\n\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\nclass Filter extends React.Component {\r\n\r\n  constructor() {\r\n    super();\r\n    this.state = {\r\n      searchState: {...qs.parse(document.location.search.slice(1)) }\r\n    };\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  onSearchStateChange(nextState) {\r\n    // the next line causes my component to render again and again. \r\n    this.setState({ searchState: nextState });\r\n    window.history.replaceState({}, \"\", `?${qs.stringify(nextState)}`);\r\n  }\r\n  createURL(state) {\r\n    return `?${qs.stringify(state)}`;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  render() {\r\n    console.log(\"rendering\");\r\n    const {\r\n      category_slug = \"\",\r\n      brand_slug = \"\"\r\n    } = this.props.params;\r\n\r\n    return (\r\n      <InstantSearch\r\n        appId={ALGOLIA_APPID}\r\n        apiKey={ALGOLIA_APIKEY}\r\n        indexName={MAININDEX}\r\n        searchState={this.state.searchState}\r\n        onSearchStateChange={this.onSearchStateChange.bind(this)}>\r\n\r\n        <div>\r\n        {/* Some Refinements */}\r\n        </div>\r\n      </InstantSearch>\r\n    );\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```",
